fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.models.interfaces

Interface CoupledModelI

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ModelDescriptionI, ModelI, ParentNotificationI
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CoupledModel, MoleneModel, PortableComputerModel, WiFiModel

    public interface CoupledModelI
extends ModelI, ParentNotificationI
    The interface CoupledModelI defines the most generic methods to be implemented by DEVS atomic simulation models.

    Description

    Invariant

      • select

        java.lang.String select(java.lang.String[] candidates)
        when a coupled model is performing an internal step and more than one submodel tie for the next internal step, return the URI of the model that should do so, breaking the tie.

        Description

        Users must implement this method when their coupled models can exhibit such tied internal transitions, otherwise an implementation performing either a random selection for non HIOA models or selecting a HIOA model having no dependencies is provided by the abstract class.

        Contract

         pre     candidates != null && candidates.length > 1
 post   true            // no postcondition.
        Parameters:
        candidates - URIs of the candidates submodels for the next internal transition.
        Returns:
        the URI of model that will perform its internal transition, breaking the tie.
